objects.name: Nohoval Cove
objects.description: Close to the village Nohoval lies a small bay, which is a real eye-catcher due to its steep cliffs and some rocks rising from the sea â€“ the Nohoval Cove. Once you have reached the bay via a narrow country road, you first notices the ruins of an old slate mine. On the opposite slope a path leads up to the cliffs. From here you can enjoy the best view over the bay.

objects.name: Royal Cork Yacht Club
objects.description: The Royal Cork Yacht Club is a claimant to the title of the world's oldest yacht club, founded in 1720, although some consider the Neva Yacht Club to be older by two years. It is presently located in Crosshaven, Co. Cork, Ireland.
